💚 Dreams do come true in New Orleans 💚

✨
✨
✨

First announced at D23 Expo 2022, Tiana’s Palace Restaurant is coming to Disneyland later this year! 

It will replace the French Market restaurant and actually have its exterior inspired by the actual one located in New Orleans. This means French Market and the Mint Julep bar will close on Feb 17th to start making this happen.

Not to worry though! The menu will still serve up classic favorites while expanding on even more Louisiana cuisine with tiana flair! And Mint Julep Bar will return as well. 

The restaurant will be quick service and no character dining which is fine since tiana strolls the square and takes rides on the Mark Twain, so you’ll catch her eventually. 

This comes along the heels of Eudora’s Chic Boutique ft Tiana’s Gourmet Secrets shop in New Orleans Square, following Tiana’s Bayou Adventure, set to replace Splash Mountain and open in 2024. More details can be found on Disney Parks Blog! 

Who’s ready to finally try some of Tiana’s homecooking? And where should they put her restaurant in Walt Disney World?
